            data_html:
              "<table><tr><th>candidate_name</th><td>Alice Martin</td></tr><tr><th>overall_score</th><td>93</td></tr><tr><th>decision</th><td>interview</td></tr><tr><th>interview_questions</th><td><ul><li><table><tr><th>question</th><td>Can you walk us through the architecture of the microservices platform you built at TechCorp? Specifically, how did you decide on the boundaries between services, and how did Python and Go each play a role in your technology choices?</td></tr><tr><th>assessment_goal</th><td>Confirm depth of knowledge in microservices architecture and validate proficiency in both Python and Go, ensuring the candidate can make informed technical decisions about language selection and system design \u2014 a core requirement for the Senior Software Engineer role.</td></tr></table></li><li><table><tr><th>question</th><td>Tell me about a time when you had to mentor or guide a junior engineer through a challenging technical problem. What was the situation, what actions did you take, and what was the outcome?</td></tr><tr><th>assessment_goal</th><td>Assess leadership and mentoring capability using the STAR behavioral format. This evaluates the candidate&#x27;s ability to lead and develop junior engineers, which is a key requirement of the role and critical for team growth within the platform team.</td></tr></table></li><li><table><tr><th>question</th><td>Your CV mentions designing CI/CD pipelines that reduced deployment time by 60%. Can you describe the specific tools, stages, and strategies you implemented? How did you handle rollback scenarios and ensure reliability in your deployment process on AWS with Docker and Kubernetes?</td></tr><tr><th>assessment_goal</th><td>Evaluate deep technical competency in CI/CD, containerization (Docker/Kubernetes), and cloud infrastructure (AWS). This probes the intersection of several core job requirements and nice-to-have criteria to confirm hands-on expertise rather than surface-level familiarity.</td></tr></table></li><li><table><tr><th>question</th><td>At StartupXYZ, you built real-time data processing pipelines handling 10K events per second. How would you approach designing a similar system today using cloud-native services on AWS? What trade-offs would you consider regarding latency, throughput, and cost?</td></tr><tr><th>assessment_goal</th><td>Assess technical depth in real-time data processing (a nice-to-have skill) and the candidate&#x27;s ability to apply evolving cloud-native best practices. This also evaluates architectural thinking, scalability awareness, and cost-consciousness \u2014 important traits for a senior engineer on a platform team.</td></tr></table></li><li><table><tr><th>question</th><td>How do you typically collaborate with cross-functional teams (e.g., product managers, DevOps, QA) when delivering a complex feature? Can you share an example where differing priorities or opinions within the team required you to find a compromise or drive alignment?</td></tr><tr><th>assessment_goal</th><td>Assess cultural and team fit, communication skills, and the candidate&#x27;s ability to navigate collaboration challenges. Since the role involves joining a platform team and visiting client sites, strong interpersonal skills and the ability to align diverse stakeholders are essential.</td></tr></table></li></ul></td></tr></table>",
